<title>HONG KONG: Grande Holdings 1996 net rises 65 pct.</title>
<headline>Grande Holdings 1996 net rises 65 pct.</headline>
<dateline>HONG KONG 1997-05-27</dateline>
<text>
<p>Year ended December 31</p>
<p>(in million HK$ unless stated)</p>
<p>    Shr (H.K. cents)	   55.0	vs 33.0</p>
<p>    Dividend (H.K. cents)    10.0	vs 5.0</p>
<p>    Exceptional items	  29.0 loss vs 55.0 gain</p>
<p>    Net			    140.0     vs 85.0</p>
<p>    Turnover		     6,367.0   vs 6,076.0</p>
<p>    Company name		 Grande Holdings Ltd</p>
<p>    Books close		  June 17-24</p>
<p>    Dividend payable	   July 23</p>
<p>NOTE - Grande Holdings makes computer components and electronic products.</p>
<p>Net is after an exceptional loss of HK$33 million in relation to non-core activities terminated during the year, loss of HK$82 million from operations of non-strategic investments divested subsequent to the year-end, loss of HK$18 million by subsidiary under restructuring and provision for possible losses on liquidation of such subsidiary and gain of HK$104 million on partial divestment of interests in certain subsidiaries and associated companies.</p>
<p>Total dividend for year is 15 H.K. cents (including interim dividend of five cents) vs 10 cents.</p>
<p>-- Hong Kong Newsroom (852) 2843 6368</p>
